<sec id="id-7004a606-408d-4581-c4b7-7c00eddde914"><title><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="68b019e3-4417-436d-e6ef-18cd776c77e8" timestamp="1627497522993"?>Privacy Protection Principle 3: Identifying Purposes<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="68b019e3-4417-436d-e6ef-18cd776c77e8"?></title><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="644c59e2-ba31-4fc7-a7f5-8169ef654ccd" timestamp="1627497663716"?><bold>Rule 009:</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="644c59e2-ba31-4fc7-a7f5-8169ef654ccd"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="3fdf0084-57d6-49bc-bfd5-9beea2996ea8" timestamp="1627497663716"?><bold>The specified purpose(s) for which personal information is collected with respect to the (the (potential) goal of the <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-e12adf88-bd24-4f73-992f-e961d98ac751.xml#id-2b6390ff-eab6-4da4-eefa-fa2c027814c7" ref-type="other" id="id-9fe56a5e-ba1e-49a1-8fa9-acc99a750ca8" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema">learning transaction</xref> shall be identified by the <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-1a4d68fc-fe38-4eca-bc35-f5899b10ac38.xml#id-c179fe60-c24b-4f61-ebaa-a0ac746bb8f6" ref-type="other" id="id-21f08089-390b-4eec-949e-5e5a36fbc978" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema">LET provider</xref> at or before the personal information is collected.</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="3fdf0084-57d6-49bc-bfd5-9beea2996ea8"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="a7baf12b-3b97-4aca-dae0-35f510b53cc7" timestamp="1627497663716"?>The specified purpose is deemed to be the goal of the <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-e12adf88-bd24-4f73-992f-e961d98ac751.xml#id-2b6390ff-eab6-4da4-eefa-fa2c027814c7" ref-type="other" id="id-59872bd1-733f-462a-ea50-c5a426cff80a" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema">learning transaction</xref>, i.e., that which is mutually agreed to by the <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-81c8b270-08f9-4f45-90a9-a2f64e3a2a96.xml#id-7542f352-d207-4a58-e060-8f75a53eae3f" ref-type="other" id="id-d57f458b-ed80-4d2c-cd9a-0edf31b9c18e" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema">individual learner</xref> and <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-1a4d68fc-fe38-4eca-bc35-f5899b10ac38.xml#id-c179fe60-c24b-4f61-ebaa-a0ac746bb8f6" ref-type="other" id="id-73808711-40d2-4e2b-f07e-035d81a9b3e5" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema">LET provider</xref> at the end of the negotiation phase (and prior to the actualization) phase.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="a7baf12b-3b97-4aca-dae0-35f510b53cc7"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="45bd2d76-558d-4fce-826f-c63c9df738ae" timestamp="1627511511456"?>In an Open-edi context, the purpose for which the personal information is being collected is specified as (part of) the purpose of an Open-edi scenario, i.e., as the OeS purpose. The Clause <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-58affb80-6090-40d2-baab-441809f1cc88.xml#id-172b5700-c8b5-4794-fd82-272f605d8dc2" ref-type="sec" id="id-c616243e-8ff2-41f8-a0f6-2a0e5852c34e" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="45bd2d76-558d-4fce-826f-c63c9df738ae"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="6861742" change-id="f166aafd-6394-433e-861e-5b1823b7d0ad" timestamp="1633269057357"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f166aafd-6394-433e-861e-5b1823b7d0ad"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="32fb8df5-2d2a-44fd-edb5-e03c6df1475e" timestamp="1627511511456"?>Rules for scoping <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-971ccf2f-deae-47b0-8cf5-ede742e9a764.xml#id-41a20382-e6d6-4570-b73d-cb5559fc9d13" ref-type="other" id="id-bb1c8d4f-3ba6-4ff1-dcc0-a45a531bb70c" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema">Open-edi</xref> scenarios in ISO/IEC 15944-1 already make provision for supporting this rule from a privacy protection requirements perspective.<sup><xref ref-type="fn" as:rid="chunks/82851/id-6a6c5f54-264f-41d4-bc3d-a3ac6a712589.xml#id-b9b44ebf-58da-4f85-c310-699fe05529c7" id="id-0021d76e-6f89-46ed-c30d-1cd504e817d4" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref><fn id="id-b9b44ebf-58da-4f85-c310-699fe05529c7"><p>See further below Clause 12.3 “<italic>Template for specifying an Open-edi scenario”</italic> of privacy protection requirements” in ISO/IEC 15944-8.</p></fn></sup><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="32fb8df5-2d2a-44fd-edb5-e03c6df1475e"?></p><p/><p/></sec>
